write_do_lec_innovus(25.10)                        write_do_lec_innovus(25.10)

Name
       write_do_lec_innovus - Writes out the dofile for the Conformal(R) Logi-
       cal Equivalence Checker tool

Syntax
       write_do_lec_innovus

       [-help]

       <output_filename>

       [-checkpoint <lec_checkpoint_file>]

       [-golden_design <filename>]

       [-log_file <filename>]

       [-no_exit]

       [-pre_compare <filename>]

       [-pre_exit <filename>]

       [-pre_read <filename>]

       [-revised_design <filename>]

       [-verbose]

       [-write_session <lec_session_name>]

       {-hier | -flat }

       > <output_filename>

       Writes  out the dofile for the Conformal(R) Logical Equivalence Checker
       tool.

       For  formal  verification  of  the  Innovus-generated   netlists,   the
       write_do_lec_innovus  command  generates, within Innovus, the Conformal
       LEC scripts (such as dofile). These scripts are  used  for  equivalence
       checking.  You can generate a flat or a hierarchical comparison script.
       The dofile written out by this command contains standard Conformal flow
       commands and you will need to add the DFT  constraints  if  netlist  is
       scan inserted.

       The  write_do_lec_innovus  command creates a verification directory, if
       does not already exist, in which the name mapping information file will
       be created. The name mapping file will usually contain the mapping  in-
       formation  of MBIT flops against its split/single bit candidate. By de-
       fault, the name of this verification directory is fv/invs/%s.  You  can
       use write_lec_directory_naming_style to change the directory name.

Parameters
       -help  Prints  a  brief  description that includes the type and default
              information for each write_do_lec_innovus parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man write_do_lec_innovus

       <output_filename>
              Specifies the name for the output file to be written.

       -checkpoint <lec_checkpoint_file>
              Specifies the name of the LEC checkpoint file  to  save  at  the
              end.

       -flat  Creates a flat comparison script.

       -golden_design <filename>
              Specifies  the  user-written  netlist  file  name  to use as the
              golden design.

       -hier  Creates a hierarchical comparison script.

       -log_file <filename>
              Specifies the name of the LEC log file.

       -no_exit
              Skips the exit command at end of dofile.

       -pre_compare <filename>
              Specifies an extra dofile to be sourced right before 'compare'.

       -pre_exit <filename>
              Specifies an extra dofile to be sourced right before 'exit'.

       -pre_read <filename>
              Specifies an extra dofile to be sourced right before reading li-
              brary/design.

       -revised_design <filename>
              Specifies the user-written netlist file name to use as  the  re-
              vised design.

       -verbose
              Specifies whether the generated dofile will report verbosely.

       -write_session <lec_session_name>
              Specifies the name of the LEC session to save at the end.

       > <output_filename>
              Specifies the name for the output file to be written.

